      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Legend\n- contract node: working meaning for a template-structure class\n- boundary note: what this set should not become"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Template Structure Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": -980,
        "y": 20
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Template Structure Contract\n\nThis is a working v1 contract for a reusable template-structure nodeset.\n\nThe job of this set is template anatomy, not final document content and not domain semantics.\n\nStructural law:\n- `title` names\n- `section` organizes\n- `slot` requests content\n- `instruction` guides authorship\n- `example` demonstrates\n- `constraint` bounds"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-title",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "title",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": -40
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# title\n\nNames the template or a major template part.\n\n- provides framing, not fill-in content\n- should be used sparingly\n- gives the reader immediate orientation"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-section",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "section",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": -180
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# section\n\nGroups a coherent part of the template.\n\n- defines a region of purpose\n- may contain slots, instructions, examples, and constraints\n- answers how the template is divided"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-slot",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "slot",
      "position": {
        "x": 620,
        "y": -180
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# slot\n\nDeclares a place that should be filled with real content.\n\n- answers what belongs here\n- should usually point toward domain content\n- should not become a big content container by default"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-instruction",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "instruction",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": 140
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# instruction\n\nTells a human or agent how to fill a slot or section.\n\n- procedural or editorial guidance\n- not itself required output content\n- answers how this should be authored"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-example",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "example",
      "position": {
        "x": 620,
        "y": 140
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# example\n\nShows a good instance of what a filled slot or section might look like.\n\n- illustrative, not canonical\n- should remain subordinate to the slot it helps explain\n- answers what good looks like"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-constraint",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "constraint",
      "position": {
        "x": 1080,
        "y": -20
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# constraint\n\nStates what must be true or what must be avoided.\n\n- applies limits, quality bars, or structural rules\n- should be inspectable and reusable\n- answers what must stay within bounds"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-boundaries",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Important Boundaries",
      "position": {
        "x": 1080,
        "y": 300
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Important Boundaries\n\n- `section` vs `slot`\n  - section is a region\n  - slot is a fill point\n\n- `instruction` vs `example`\n  - instruction tells\n  - example shows\n\n- `constraint` vs `instruction`\n  - constraint is a rule\n  - instruction is guidance\n\n## Non-goal\n\nThis set should not become a second document model and should not replace domain nodes like `task`, `claim`, or `feature`."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "template-structure-contract-back",
      "type": "port",
      "label": "Back to Template / Structure Task",
      "position": {
        "x": -980,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 320,
